# VoteChain UI Rules

All UI must exactly match **Google Stitch designs** exported to `design/stitch-screens/`.

## Golden Rule

**Do not redesign any screen.** Implement what Stitch specifies — pixel-faithful, token-driven, component-based.

## Design Tokens (Must Stay Consistent)

| Token | Flutter (`mobile/lib/theme/`) | React (`admin/src/theme/`) |
|-------|-------------------------------|----------------------------|
| Colors | `ColorScheme` from Stitch palette | CSS variables / MUI theme |
| Typography | `TextTheme` — no inline font overrides | Theme typography scale |
| Icons | Material Symbols matching Stitch | Same icon set as Flutter |
| Border Radius | `BorderRadius` constants in theme | Theme border-radius tokens |
| Elevation | Material 3 elevation levels | MUI elevation / box-shadow tokens |
| Spacing | 4dp / 8dp grid system | Same spacing scale (4px / 8px) |

## Flutter UI

- **Material 3 only** — no legacy Material 2 widgets.
- Build screens by composing reusable widgets from `mobile/lib/widgets/`.
- Map each Stitch screen to a feature presentation screen.
- Keep animations **subtle** — use Material motion defaults, no flashy transitions.

## React Admin UI

- Match the same visual language as Flutter — shared color palette and spacing.
- Extract shared patterns into reusable components under `admin/src/components/`.
- Use the same naming conventions for equivalent UI elements across both apps.

## Component Rules

- Create **reusable components** — buttons, cards, input fields, status badges, avatars.
- Never duplicate UI code across features — promote to `widgets/` or `components/`.
- Reference Stitch screen filename when implementing: `// Stitch: login_screen.png`.

## Anti-Patterns

```dart
// ❌ Hardcoded styling
Container(
  color: Color(0xFF1A73E8),
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(13),
  child: Text('Vote', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 17)),
)

// ✅ Theme-driven styling
Container(
  color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary,
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(AppSpacing.md),
  child: Text('Vote', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleMedium),
)
```

## Before Implementing a Screen

1. Open the corresponding Stitch export in `design/stitch-screens/`.
2. Identify reusable components already built — reuse before creating new ones.
3. Implement in this priority order: **Layout → Spacing → Typography → Colors → Icons → Animations → Business Logic**.
4. Implement using theme tokens only.
5. Do not add, remove, or rearrange UI elements unless explicitly requested.
6. Add file comment: `// Stitch: <screen_name>.png`.
